Adelaide Crows captain Taylor 'Tex' Walker was pictured offering a helping hand to Satine Cahill . 
  Satine was serving as the team's mascot ahead of their match against North Melbourne at Adelaide Oval on Sunday . 
  She burst into tears just moments before leading the AFL side onto the field . 
  The pig-tailed youngster became spooked by the fireworks and rumbling fans . 
  Tex quickly stepped up to help calm Satine down before taking her hand and walking with her on the pitch . 
  The touching moment was captured by photographers . 
 